Note: ===================================================================
Note: MATLAB LEXER
Note: ===================================================================
Note: Lexical analysis for MATLAB (Matrix Laboratory) - scientific
Note: and engineering computing language.

Note: MATLAB is a matrix-oriented language designed for numerical
Note: computing, data analysis, algorithm development, and visualization.

Note: Key features:
Note: - Matrix/array-oriented programming (core paradigm)
Note: - Element-wise operations (.*, ./, .^, etc.)
Note: - Advanced indexing (logical, linear, subscript)
Note: - Function handles and anonymous functions
Note: - Object-oriented programming (classdef)
Note: - Vectorization and broadcasting
Note: - Graphics and plotting

Note: Part of the Translation Translation System
Note: Location: compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/matlab/matlab_lexer.runa
Note: ===================================================================

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as ListCore

Note: ===================================================================
Note: TOKEN TYPE CONSTANTS
Note: ===================================================================

Note: Keywords (100-199)
Constant TOKEN_FUNCTION as Integer is 100
Constant TOKEN_END as Integer is 101
Constant TOKEN_IF as Integer is 102
Constant TOKEN_ELSE as Integer is 103
Constant TOKEN_ELSEIF as Integer is 104
Constant TOKEN_FOR as Integer is 105
Constant TOKEN_WHILE as Integer is 106
Constant TOKEN_SWITCH as Integer is 107
Constant TOKEN_CASE as Integer is 108
Constant TOKEN_OTHERWISE as Integer is 109
Constant TOKEN_TRY as Integer is 110
Constant TOKEN_CATCH as Integer is 111
Constant TOKEN_BREAK as Integer is 112
Constant TOKEN_CONTINUE as Integer is 113
Constant TOKEN_RETURN as Integer is 114
Constant TOKEN_GLOBAL as Integer is 115
Constant TOKEN_PERSISTENT as Integer is 116
